Description:
‘Rural’ Serenity In Town!
Experience the best of both worlds! From a big block size, a gorgeous rural-style view, to a central location in popular Drysdale, this charming home is the answer for house-hunters looking for more space close to town!
Set on over 700 sqm (approx.), the feeling of space is enhanced by the calm, semi-rural style outlook to the rear, and peaceful walking trails beyond the back gate! Close to the Bellarine Rail Trail, Lake Lorne Reserve, Drysdale Recreation Reserve, major bus routes, shopping precinct, and schools, this location puts the ‘c’ in ‘central’!
Inside, the comfortable floorplan blends indoor and outdoor living, with the lounge and balcony overlooking the green, tree-dotted expanse of neighbouring properties. The open-plan kitchen, living and dining area sits at the heart of the home. The kitchen has a practical walk-in pantry and leads into the compact home office. The master bedroom has an en suite and built-in storage, while two kids bedrooms (with built-in robes) access the bathroom and separate toilet. Other features include SS-AC and polished floorboards.
Extensive parking and storage is a huge plus- with two carports, a secure lock-up garage and large workshop offering a bounty of space for vehicles, boat and trailer, and your hobbies and projects.
With space aplenty, and a view that most would kill for this close to town, this family home is something very special! Inspect to appreciate.
Insights: 11 De Burgh Road, Drysdale VIC 3222 was last sold in 2016 and 22 other 3 bedroom house in Drysdale have recently been sold.

Description:
Large on entertaining
A large residence ideally suited for large families who need multiple living zones, great outdoor entertaining, large yard with trailer /boat/ caravan access, work shop & swimming pool.
Welcoming bullnose verandah opening to a wide entry hall.
Large formal lounge with slow combustion wood heater. Separate study or library.
Open plan kitchen with north facing casual dining area overlooking the large tiled dining room. Kitchen with a large island bench, wall oven, gas hotplates & dishwasher.
The third lounge is super sized with large windows creating a light filled entertaining area, offering plenty of room & flexibility either as a rumpus, games, or billiards.
Excellent North facing under covering alfresco entertaining area to enjoy outdoor living & BBQ's all year round.
The feature cut out walls offer a sense of openness, allowing easy viewing from the kitchen to the living areas, outdoor alfresco, backyard & swimming pool.
Master bedroom with double entry doors, ensuite & walk in robe, plus three double sized bedrooms with built in robes.
An inground swimming pool with solar heating & paved edging so you can enjoy the warmer months with a relaxed lifestyle.
Double garage with access to the alfresco area.
High carport offering easy access to the rear yard.
Man cave / utility shed ideal for the home handyman.
Situated on 804 sqm there is plenty of open space for the children to play. This beautiful residence has nothing is on a small scale.
Located in a modern estate within metres of the Bellarine Rail trail, easy access to St Ignatius College, Bellarine Secondary and the town centre.

Description:
Tranquil By Name And Nature
Central Walk Drysdale offers local boutique estate living at its best! A limited & exclusive offering of only 200 (approx) quality lots, exceptional parks & wetlands & only 200m to Drysdale's thriving retail hub. No 18 Tranquil Terrace sits effortlessly in the green leafy setting & has absolute frontage to the local wetlands reserve. Boasting 4 generous bedrooms (master with ensuite & walk in robe) all additional bedrooms complete with built in robes. A light & bright kitchen oozes style with stone bench tops, featuring industrial style light fixtures and quality appliances. The tiled family/meals area is bathed in natural light & offers a seamless connection to an expansive decked outdoor entertaining zone. An 'oversized' second separate living area offers plenty of space for the growing family. With all the modern comforts; ducted heating, evaporative cooling, landscaped low maintenance gardens (synthetic turf) & 'side access' for the boat or caravan, makes this property a must see for those buyers wanting a home offering clever practical design, great finishes and 'bang for their buck'.

Description:
Your new coastal life awaits!
This attractive coastal precinct, set in the heart of Drysdale, embodies the contemporary trend of a 'designer coastal lifestyle'.
The established estate is treed and undulating, featuring quiet courts close to local schools, shops and recreational reserves as well as the potentially outstanding bay views (STCA). Rich with native flora and fauna, this land has a relaxed coastal feel with in vogue homes set on spacious blocks. This allotment, of 720 sqm approx., sits quietly in a desirable location with little through traffic. It boasts an Easterly outlook to the kerb and fantastic morning sun to the North. The long northern aspect is ideal for contemporary architecture with plenty of winter sun filling multiple living spaces. The lovely leafy outlook and niches for native birds throughout the streets are magnificent.
This block neighbours attractive properties with an appreciation of privacy and space. And, with no fixed timeframe for commencement, it's ready for you to plan your dream home!
Live at the gateway of the Geelong & the Bellarine Peninsula, within earshot of the bay. Close to a choice of schools, great family amenities and the beach. 20' to Geelong. 90' to Melbourne.
Create your designer lifestyle here!
* 720 sqm block in a desirable coastal street in the heart of Drysdale
* Quiet, treed, undulating streets perfect for raising a family
* Close to a choice of schools, great family amenities and the beach
* Easterly outlook to the kerb, take in the northern sunlight to the living
* Long northern boundary for contemporary light-filled architecture
* Create a coastal lifestyle at the gateway to Geelong & the Bellarine Peninsula

Description:
Love This Lifestyle on the Bellarine
Gorae Downs
Looking for that special lifestyle that only open spaces, fresh country air and views to Bass Strait can provide then look no further. This property has been held by the current owners for several decades and has provided them with an enviable lifestyle for the whole family. The homely three bedroom, one bathroom farm house incorporates a second living area with outdoor verandah where you can sit and watch the ships sail by. Inside the solid fuel wood heater provides a warming and homely atmosphere for those cold winter days.
Currently used as a successful cattle stud there is ample shedding, cattle yards, cattle race and crush. Internally fenced to accommodate approximately 12 paddocks with water off a central lane way. The property would be suitable for all intensive agricultural pursuits and is close to the Drysdale shopping centre, local schools, surf beaches and the best of the Bellarine lifestyle.
The property is located on a made road with town water connected. Contact agent to arrange inspection. This property will attract immediate enquiry.
Rhonda Humpage : 0457 313 609

Description:
Central Drysdale Opportunity!
Located in Drysdale on the sought after Bellarine Peninsula, this property presents endless opportunity. The ideal home for a family, small business from home or investor looking to be centrally located within 600m of Central Drysdale
Village. The property on a large block (approx. 750m2) features 3 bedrooms and a study, with one bedroom previously been used as a salon with its own powder room. Fully equipped kitchen with gas cooktop, ample cupboard/bench space which overlooks the meals/dining area and spacious light filled formal lounge with polished floor boards, complete with split system Heating/Cooling. Family bathroom, separate toilet and sizable laundry. Outside provides a generous private yard, large shed and single garage.The Bellarine Peninsula is a growing tourist region with many beaches, wineries, cafes and restaurants. Explore the Bellarine taste trail, ride or walk the rail trail, drive 10 mins and board the new ferry from Portarlington to the Docklands. Location is a standout with this property being a short walking distance to bus stops, schools, childcare and Drysdale Village shopping centre. With Sub-Division Potential (STCA) this property has great capital growth potential. An inspection is a must for you to appreciate all this property has to offer!

HOME IS NO. 90 , SO WARM AND APPEALING , WITH APPROX. 860 SQM LAND.
Meticulously maintained, beautiful home in the heart of DRYSDALE, generous proportions in all rooms as well as north facing extra-large back yard block. This well-established 3 bedroom rendered brick home has gracious entrance, large formal lounge plus open plan dining and family room. Well-appointed kitchen with meals area, natural light floods through the living areas. The family room has access to the outdoor patio and overlooks the leafy matured gardens, fernery... so private. En-suite in master with spa, all double bedrooms with built-in robes. Features so much storage, gas fire & wall furnace, fans, split system, dishwasher, quality fittings, double garage and garden shed. This is one of the best spots in town with schools Rail Trail, shops and leisure activities all within walking distance. A pearl!

Perfection.
Check out this immaculate 2-bedroom townhouse in a prime Drysdale location. There?s certainly no exaggeration in saying that this townhouse is the best quality and value small home on the market right now.

Description:
VENDOR SAYS "MAKE US AN OFFER"
If it is space that you are after, this gorgeous split level home offers an abundance both inside and out.
Situated close to the coast, and near Geelong's finest Bellarine wineries this quality built home is perfect for the growing family and the entertainer at heart.
Thoughtfully designed, this home is warm, spacious and has a functional split level design. Best of all, the home is situated on a fantastic sized block for families who want some space for the kids to play, all in a safe fully fenced environment.
Featuring gorgeous timber flooring and a fabulous relaxing open plan lounge area with a gas log fire, this home has a lovely ambience. Additionally the fully featured kitchen is perfectly equipped for the entertainer, with a quality 900mm oven and a large adjoining meals area. Indoor/outdoor living is achieved through the lounge/meals area extending outside to a great sized undercover deck, perfect for all weather entertaining and children's outdoor play.
The home has 4 bedrooms and 3 of these bedrooms have been thoughtfully located on the upper level with their own stylish family bathroom & sep WC. Downstairs the master bedroom enjoys a large WIR & ensuite. A perfect set up for families who would like to dedicate a separate area for their kids to sleep and play.
With the beach close by and only short walk to the local school and shops and easy access to the Bellarine rail trail all, this property is a perfect solution to those seeking a perfect family home in an ideal position.

Description:
Lifestyle Just Under An Acre!
Located close to the Bellarine Rail Trail, 25-27 Station Street will not disappoint those looking to buy that unique property with all that Drysdale has to offer.
Upon entry, you are greeted with a large formal lounge with a beautiful wood fire heater that keeps the whole family and kitchen areas warm with ease. The kitchen has been fully renovated with stainless steel appliances throughout and has an amazing outlook overlooking the backyard. The home has two separate living areas and a study so that the family definitely have plenty of options to find that quiet space.
Comprising of five oversized bedrooms with built in robes, a sixth bedroom/study with built in robes and the master having a walk in robe, this home has all the bases covered for the growing family.
The home has well maintained and established gardens with plenty of scope to be able to add what is already there. With a resort style pool and spa area and with the added bonus of a wood fire pizza oven this would be the perfect summer entertaining area.
Extensive shedding and the ability to park and store multiple caravans and boats with ease and 25,000 litres of water storage that have pumps to irrigate the garden. The possibility to do a battleaxe subdivision STCA is another option for this property. This is a rare opportunity as these types of properties donâ??t come on to the market very often and with all that the Bellarine has to offer at your doorstep as well. An inspection is a must for you to fully appreciate all that this property has to offer.

Description:
The Perfect Country Retreat in Idyllic Drysdale!
Embrace the laid-back lifestyle you've been dreaming of in charming Drysdale! Whether you're looking for a country retreat to escape to on weekends, a gorgeous holiday rental to add to your portfolio, or a home to raise your family far away from the hustle and bustle of the city, this property is the one for you!
This delightful weatherboard home is in a perfect position for exploring the magical surrounding countryside. Spend weekends relishing in the abundance of wineries nearby or soaking up the sunshine as you walk the Bellarine Rail Trail. Treat yourself to a picnic at Lake Lorne Reserve or simply walk to the High Street shops and cafes for a lazy brunch. A short drive will find you sinking holes at the Curlewis Golf Club, hitting the surf at Ocean Grove, or gearing up for your next boating adventure at Clifton Springs. With so much on offer, locations don't get better than this! An array of local schools and close access to public transport makes for an effortless family lifestyle.
With freshly painted interiors, near-new carpet and polished floorboards throughout, this home is ready for you to move in and enjoy. The light, airy character of the open plan living zone makes this the perfect place to both relax and entertain guests. Bi-fold glass doors welcome in the natural light and open up to the northeast facing wrap-around deck - creating the ideal indoor-outdoor fusion for warm summer months. Spend endless summer evenings lounging on the deck while listening to the delightful sounds of birdlife, or snuggle up to the gas log fire with a glass of red in the chilly winter months.
The sparkling new kitchen boasts 2-pak gloss cabinetry, soft close cupboards, and stainless steel appliances including a wall oven, gas hob, rangehood, and dishwasher. A built-in pantry, ample storage, and generous bench space means you'll never run out space again.
A separate lounge and dining room allow for alternative entertaining options and offer family members a relaxing retreat.
Graced with expansive built-in robes and en suite, the master bedroom is a haven for parents with private access to the deck. Two additional bedrooms are zoned to the front of the home and share easy access to the main bathroom.
Brand new zoned ducted heating, two gas log fires, a split system heating and cooling device, and ceiling fans throughout keep you comfortable in all seasons.
Complete with electricity and sash windows, the outdoor bungalow offers immense versatility as a studio, kids play space or teenage retreat. Children and pets will adore roaming freely in the secure and private yard, while cooking enthusiasts will love using fresh produce straight from the veggie patches.
A remote single lock-up garage offers secure off-street parking and plentiful room for storage.
A soothing retreat from your busy city life, this home offers wineries, beaches and golf courses moments from your front door! Indulge in a country holiday home moments from the coast, invest in a serene holiday rental, or move here full time for a hassle-free family lifestyle! Inspect ASAP!
Land size 710m2 (approx).
